        "description": {
            "en": "This course dives into the concept of token efficiency using coding agents like GitHub Copilot and Cursor. You'll explore why token efficiency matters for cost-effective and faster coding, and learn how tools like Cursor use an 'Auto' mode to automatically route each request to the most appropriate AI model \u2014 saving tokens on simple tasks without sacrificing quality on complex ones. You'll also learn how to apply the same model-selection principles manually in GitHub Copilot. Additionally, you'll gain insights into best practices for managing token usage and understand why relying on the most powerful models isn't always ideal. Designed for beginners, this short 15-minute course equips you with practical skills to leverage coding agents effectively, saving time and resources in your development workflow."
